There should be 3 different classes:

Reform Mat Pilates (stock 6 per class, 2 classes) Wed 930AM, Friday 1045AM

Rebound Circuit Pilates (stock 6 per class, 2 classes) Wed 1045AM, Friday 930AM

Realign Vinyasa Yoga (Stock 7 per class, 2 classes)


Pilates Description info:

Pilates classes at RedoHealth are mat-based and use a combination of strengthening and stretching exercises. All classes will include the use of small Pilates-type equipment (Magic circle, balls, bands, small weights).

Pilates with a Certified Pilates Instructor is great for helping those with neck and back pain, shoulder pain, hip pain, knee pain, those recovering from an injury, those looking to prevent injury or those wanting to improve their posture and strength.

In our Pilates classes you will:

  1. Rebuild strength of postural muscles
  2. Restore mobility
  3. Reduce muscle tension in chronically tight areas.
  4. Reconnect with your deep muscular system effectively and efficiently (core)
  5. Recover from injury
  6. Reduce your risk of future injury.

Prior to starting your class, all NEW participants will be assessed for your postural and movement strategies to identify areas that require specific attention. This allows for your individual differences to be addressed with the appropriate exercises.
